HEADWORD: Metatarsus
<hw>Met`a*tar"sus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Metatarsi</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. See <er>Meta-</er>,
and <er>Tarsus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>That part of the
skeleton of the hind or lower limb between the tarsus and phalanges;
metatarse. It consists, in the human foot, of five bones. See
<xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

